<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_script` (Business Rule)
    row that auto-populates the `opened_date` field on every newly inserted
    `x_casemgmt_case` record inside the scoped application `x_casemgmt`.

    PURPOSE (AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim):
        "opened_date  |  DateTime  |  Auto-set on creation"

    This Business Rule is the ServiceNow-native equivalent of ArkCase's JPA
    @PrePersist beforeInsert() audit hook in
    acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/com/
    armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java (lines 307-316). The
    ArkCase hook ran before Hibernate persisted a new `acm_case_file` row
    and defaulted any unpopulated `status` field to "DRAFT". Status defaulting
    is handled in ServiceNow at the dictionary level (default_value="Draft" on
    ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_status.xml) rather than in this Business
    Rule; this Business Rule's sole responsibility is the `opened_date` audit
    timestamp. The corresponding ArkCase audit field was the `created` column
    (java.util.Date with @Temporal(TIMESTAMP)) on the AcmEntity superclass;
    the ServiceNow domain-meaningful equivalent is the `opened_date` field on
    `x_casemgmt_case` (note that ServiceNow auto-manages the platform audit
    column `sys_created_on` automatically on every record - this Business Rule
    only populates the DOMAIN-meaningful `opened_date` business field, not
    the platform audit column).

    BEHAVIOR:
        - Trigger          : BEFORE INSERT only on the `x_casemgmt_case` table
        - Condition        : current.opened_date is nil/empty
        - Action           : sets current.opened_date = gs.nowDateTime()
        - Other timing     : does NOT fire on update, delete, or query

    DEFENSIVE FIELD-SET (AAP Section 0.4.1 dashboards consideration):
        The script uses current.opened_date.nil() to check whether the field
        is already populated. If the caller (seed data, Table API, scripted
        REST endpoint, manual administrative insert) has already provided an
        explicit opened_date value, the script does NOT overwrite. This
        intentionally allows:
            (a) Seed data demos in ../seed-data/cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_*.xml
                to specify synthetic timestamps spanning the past 30 days so
                the "Cases opened (30 days)" single-score widget on the Manager
                View dashboard (../reports/x_casemgmt_cases_opened_30d.xml) has
                non-zero data on a freshly-imported PDI.
            (b) The "Average time to close" report
                (../reports/x_casemgmt_avg_time_to_close.xml) to receive
                pre-aged demo opened_date values that pair with the seeded
                closed_date values to produce a meaningful average.
        For organic inserts (no explicit opened_date), the script populates
        the field with the current platform time so reports and the portal
        status lookup never see a null opened_date.

    DICTIONARY READ-ONLY OVERRIDE:
        The opened_date field is declared read_only=true at the dictionary
        level in ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_opened_date.xml. ServiceNow
        intentionally exempts server-side Business Rule scripts from
        dictionary read_only enforcement so this rule can write the field
        even though end-users cannot edit it on the form. This pattern is
        the canonical way to populate auto-set audit-style domain fields.

    PORTAL SUBMISSION COMPATIBILITY:
        The unauthenticated submission endpoint at
        ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_casemgmt_case_status_lookup.xml
        and the portal submission endpoint
        (../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_casemgmt_case_submit.xml when
        authored) both insert into x_casemgmt_case via GlideRecord.insert().
        The platform fires before-insert Business Rules in ALL contexts when
        is_rest=false, so this rule fires for portal submissions too. The
        external requester therefore gets a non-null opened_date populated
        automatically on Draft creation. The portal status lookup later
        exposes opened_date back to the requester as one of the three
        whitelisted fields (status, subject, opened_date) per AAP Section
        0.4.4 ("External Experience Portal UI").

    ORDERING WITHIN BEFORE-INSERT PHASE:
        order=100 is intentionally low to ensure this rule runs early in the
        before-insert phase. opened_date is populated before any subsequent
        before-insert rules (such as field-validation rules) execute, so any
        downstream rule that reads current.opened_date sees a populated
        value. There is no opened_date READ in any other before-insert rule
        in this scoped application, so the order does not currently conflict
        with anything; 100 leaves room above (lower numbers run earlier) and
        below for future expansion.

    EMAIL-DISABLED CONSTRAINT (AAP Section 0.7.2):
        The script body MUST NOT call gs.eventQueue('...') for any email
        notification event since email is disabled on the PDI. This rule
        contains zero gs.eventQueue() calls, zero gs.email() calls, and
        zero gs.notificationEngine() calls. It performs only the field-set
        operation.

    SCOPED-NAMESPACE CONSTRAINT (AAP Section 0.7.2):
        - <collection>x_casemgmt_case</collection>     scoped table
        - <sys_scope>x_casemgmt</sys_scope>            scoped namespace
        - <sys_package>x_casemgmt</sys_package>        scoped application
        - script body references current.opened_date  scoped field
        Zero global-scope writes. Zero modifications to OOB tables.

    NO-HARDCODED-SYS_ID CONSTRAINT (AAP Section 0.7.2):
        - <collection> resolves the case table BY NAME (x_casemgmt_case)
        - <sys_scope> resolves the scope record BY NAME (x_casemgmt)
        - <sys_package> resolves the application record BY NAME (x_casemgmt)
        - The script body performs ZERO GlideRecord lookups by sys_id
          literal; it operates only on the platform-injected `current`
          GlideRecord (the row being inserted).
        - The <sys_id> element below is THIS record's own deterministic
          primary key (MD5 of "x_casemgmt_set_opened_date"), which is
          permitted because the AAP "no hardcoded sys_id" rule applies to
          REFERENCE FIELDS pointing at OTHER records, not to a record's own
          primary key.

    UPDATE-SET LOAD ORDER (AAP Section 0.5.2):
        This sys_script record MUST be loaded AFTER:
            - ../tables/x_casemgmt_case.xml             (table this rule attaches to)
            - ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_opened_date.xml (field this rule writes)
            - ../app/sys_app/x_casemgmt_case_management.xml (scoped application)
            - ../app/sys_scope/x_casemgmt.xml           (scope record)
        And BEFORE:
            - ../seed-data/cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_*.xml (demo case rows insert
              into x_casemgmt_case; this BR fires for them, but the demos that
              explicitly set opened_date won't be overwritten thanks to the
              .nil() check)
            - ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_casemgmt_case_submit.xml
              (the portal submission inserts into x_casemgmt_case; this BR fires)

    DETERMINISTIC SYS_ID:
        sys_id = MD5("x_casemgmt_set_opened_date")
               = c56aeecd4086f111be2867faae9e55ad
        32-character lowercase hex. The PDI accepts any valid 32-char hex
        sys_id; deriving from the record name guarantees idempotent re-import
        on a fresh PDI: re-importing the same Update Set produces the same
        sys_id, which collides on the existing record and updates it in place
        rather than creating a duplicate.

    VALIDATION GATE MAPPING (AAP Section 0.7.3):
        - Gate 1 (Data model): "All 3 custom tables created with correct
          fields and types - Zero missing mandatory fields". This rule
          ensures opened_date is populated on every insert, supporting
          Gate 1's data integrity expectations.
        - Gate 6 (Dashboards): "Both dashboards render with synthetic
          data - All widgets display data". The "Cases opened (30 days)"
          single-score widget requires non-null opened_date values; this
          rule guarantees that for any organically inserted case.
        - Gate 7 (Update Set): "Scoped app exported - Update Set loads
          without errors on a fresh PDI instance". The deterministic
          sys_id and reference-by-name pattern ensure this rule re-imports
          cleanly with zero preview errors.
-->
<record_update table="sys_script">
    <sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <abort_action>false</abort_action>
        <access>package_private</access>
        <action_delete>false</action_delete>
        <action_insert>true</action_insert>
        <action_query>false</action_query>
        <action_update>false</action_update>
        <active>true</active>
        <add_message>false</add_message>
        <advanced>true</advanced>
        <change_fields>false</change_fields>
        <client_callable>false</client_callable>
        <collection>x_casemgmt_case</collection>
        <condition/>
        <description>Before-insert on x_casemgmt_case: sets current.opened_date = gs.nowDateTime() when not already populated. Replaces ArkCase CaseFile.@PrePersist beforeInsert() audit hook from acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java. Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (opened_date Auto-set on creation). Defensive: respects pre-set values from seed data and other authoritative callers via current.opened_date.nil() guard. Fires in all contexts (form, Table API, scripted REST, seed scripts) because is_rest=false. Order=100 ensures the field is populated early in the before-insert phase. Contains zero gs.eventQueue() calls per the email-disabled constraint.</description>
        <execute_function>false</execute_function>
        <filter_condition/>
        <is_rest>false</is_rest>
        <message/>
        <name>x_casemgmt_set_opened_date</name>
        <order>100</order>
        <priority>100</priority>
        <rest_method/>
        <rest_method_text/>
        <rest_service/>
        <rest_service_text/>
        <rest_variables/>
        <role_conditions/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
    // ServiceNow-native equivalent of ArkCase CaseFile.@PrePersist beforeInsert()
    // (acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/com/
    //  armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java, lines 307-316).
    //
    // Per AAP Section 0.5.7: opened_date is "DateTime, Auto-set on creation".
    //
    // Defensive .nil() guard: respect pre-set values from authoritative callers.
    // This is critical for the seed-data demos in
    // ../seed-data/cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_*.xml which explicitly set
    // synthetic timestamps spanning the past 30 days so the "Cases opened
    // (30 days)" single-score widget on the Manager View dashboard
    // (../reports/x_casemgmt_cases_opened_30d.xml) has non-zero data on a
    // freshly-imported PDI. Without this guard, the seeded timestamps would
    // be overwritten with gs.nowDateTime() at import time and every demo
    // case would appear to be opened on import day.
    //
    // For organic inserts (form submissions, Table API calls, portal scripted
    // REST submissions, ad-hoc admin scripts) where opened_date is not
    // pre-populated, the script populates the field with the current platform
    // time so downstream reports and the portal status lookup never see a
    // null opened_date.
    if (current.opened_date.nil()) {
        current.opened_date = gs.nowDateTime();
    }
})(current, previous);
]]></script>
        <sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name>
        <sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by>
        <sys_created_on>2025-01-01 00:00:00</sys_created_on>
        <sys_domain>global</sys_domain>
        <sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path>
        <sys_id>c56aeecd4086f111be2867faae9e55ad</sys_id>
        <sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count>
        <sys_name>x_casemgmt_set_opened_date</sys_name>
        <sys_overrides/>
        <sys_package display_value="Case Management" source="x_casemgmt">x_casemgmt</sys_package>
        <sys_policy/>
        <sys_scope display_value="Case Management">x_casemgmt</sys_scope>
        <sys_update_name>sys_script_x_casemgmt_set_opened_date</sys_update_name>
        <sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by>
        <sys_updated_on>2025-01-01 00:00:00</sys_updated_on>
        <template/>
        <when>before</when>
    </sys_script>
</record_update>
